EW4R6lgfx3M.title: adidas | Allbirds FUTURECRAFT.FOOTPRINT Made to Fit the Planet ​E04: The Art of Reduction
EW4R6lgfx3M.description:
LESS, MORE: ​

We reduced, refined and rethought every component of the shoe. We chose carbon light, recycled and natural materials for the upper. The midsole designs out the need for a torsion bar and combines bio-based adidas LIGHTSTRIKE and Allbirds SweetFoam®, made with 18% sugar cane. The outsole uses 10% natural rubber in a new process. In construction, we created pattern efficiency using the tangram principle, allowing us to piece together the shoe like a puzzle to minimize waste. Smart redesign and reductions at every step for a footprint to fit the planet.

E4dmYbknMVo.title: adidas | Allbirds FUTURECRAFT.FOOTPRINT Made to Fit the Planet ​E05: Changing Every Step
E4dmYbknMVo.description:
INNOVATIVE UNLOCKS: ​

To make a shoe that fits the planet, adidas and Allbirds had to radically rethink materials and every step in the process. In pursuit of our ambition, tier 1 factories have been moved over to renewable energy, we ensure ships that transport from factory to warehouse run on biofuel. Packaging has been redesigned to remove weight, waste and carbon. This is the first step in unlocking low carbon high-performance creation for every sport, and every product we make.

LhU6ElOY9bg.title: adidas | Allbirds FUTURECRAFT.FOOTPRINT Made to Fit the Planet ​E03: Low Carbon High-performance
LhU6ElOY9bg.description:
NO COMPROMISE FOR ATHLETE OR EARTH: ​

We maximized performance with minimum materials and smarter, multi-functional solutions. The torsion bar is replaced with a carved-out midsole that gives strategic support to the midfoot. We reimagine the shoe’s lining as 100% recycled polyester embroideries that reinforce toe box, midfoot and heel. Resulting in one of our lightest running shoes, while drastically reducing our carbon impact by 63%. Performance and planet can run side by side.

SobYG8Cd0-g.title: adidas | Allbirds FUTURECRAFT.FOOTPRINT Made to Fit the Planet ​E01: Carbon Calculation
SobYG8Cd0-g.description:
EVERY STEP MEASURED:​

FUTURECRAFT.FOOTPRINT is a first. We’ve measured carbon impact at every step. Using the Allbirds Life Cycle Assessment tool that is verified against ISO standards. From shoe-making (materials and manufacturing) through to transportation, packaging, use and end-of-life. Transforming how we create to draw down carbon wherever possible. This formula gives us the answer. The number we place on every shoe, helping athletes choose better performance and footprint, at a glance.

qj-I5zLl2y4.title: adidas | Allbirds FUTURECRAFT.FOOTPRINT Made to Fit the Planet ​E02: Collaboration Over Competition
qj-I5zLl2y4.description:
DOING BUSINESS DIFFERENTLY FOR OUR PLANET: ​

adidas and Allbirds have come together to show that when two competitors collaborate, anything is possible. Athletes no longer have to choose between performance and planet. Our ambition was to develop the lowest carbon emissions performance running shoe ever created. By opening up, sharing knowledge and resources, we have accelerated change across all fronts, rethinking every step in the process and iterating faster. Working virtually around the globe and the clock, to the speed of ideas, not travel. We’ve gone faster together than we ever could alone. Together, anything is possible.

R__xk0-z7lg.title: adidas | Stan Smith Mylo /// Made With Nature​​
R__xk0-z7lg.description:
Introducing Stan Smith Mylo  ​

The upper is partially created from Mylo material. Crafted from lab-grown mycelium, the root-like structure of mushrooms. Harnessing natural technologies, billions of years in the making to shape the future of footwear. ​

We’re pushing what's possible in sustainability. To change the way products are made. To unlock our ability to make products with nature. We’re on the journey to a world beyond plastic.​

Built With Biology​
Crafted With Humanity​
#MadeWithNature​

​#EndPlasticWaste​
#StanSmithForever​

​///​

​Find out more at https://www.adidas.com/us/blog/663481

q8lpWg0cRhY.title: adidas | End Plastic Waste | Episode 3: Made for the Future
q8lpWg0cRhY.description:
All of us influence the future. Every choice we make has an effect. We highlight the sustainable goals we are working towards in this episode - from phasing out virgin polyester, to climate neutrality. ​

Stay in the loop, subscribe to our channel. ​

​We’re developing products Made to Be Remade and exploring materials Made With Nature. Collaboration is key, because only with collective action is real change possible.​

​By 2024, we aim to be free of virgin polyester. As a signatory to the UN fashion industry Charter for Climate Action, adidas has committed to reduce both its own and its suppliers’ greenhouse gas emissions compared to 2017 by 30 percent by 2030 and to achieve climate neutrality by 2050.​

​For more information visit adidas.com/sustainability and join the conversation on Twitter and Instagram via @adidas.​

​#EndPlasticWaste​

Narration: Deanna Rodger - https://www.deannarodger.co.uk  

Explore Parley products: adidas.com/parley  | Explore Primeblue products: adidas.com/primeblue

TDfobJAck24.title: adidas | End Plastic Waste | Episode 2: Changing the Game
TDfobJAck24.description:
Our collaboration with Parley for the Oceans, how we’re innovating with them to help End Plastic Waste is the focus of this episode. It’s a relationship that has changed the game. adidas shoes made with Parley Ocean Plastic are a symbol of change.​

Stay in the loop, subscribe to our channel.​

With Parley we’re entering a new era, where we collaborate with nature. Exploring technologies that build on plant-based cells and proteins, materials that can return to nature in a regenerative loop.​

​Events like Run for the Oceans and education through Parley Ocean school are important. We all need to join the fight to help end plastic waste.​

​For more information visit adidas.com/sustainability and join the conversation on Twitter and Instagram via @adidas.​

​#EndPlasticWaste #adidasParley

Narration: Deanna Rodger - https://www.deannarodger.co.uk  

Explore Parley products: adidas.com/parley | Explore Primeblue products: adidas.com/primeblue

J2GENjc_7ac.title: adidas | End Plastic Waste | Episode 1: Breaking Point
J2GENjc_7ac.description:
​Plastic waste is a problem. In this episode we reveal the scale of it and describe what we’re doing to help End Plastic Waste. Innovation is our solution. We’ve teamed up with partners and launched a three-loop plan for real change.​

​Stay in the loop, subscribe to our channel.​

In the Recycled Loop, products are made using recycled materials. In the Circular Loop, products are Made To Be Remade, and the Regenerative Loop, we’re exploring materials Made with Nature. Each loop takes us closer to being a circular company.​

​For more information visit adidas.com/sustainability, join the conversation on Twitter and Instagram via @adidas. Read more at https://www.adidas.co.uk/blog/629060.

​#EndPlasticWaste

Narration: Deanna Rodger - https://www.deannarodger.co.uk  

Explore Parley products: adidas.com/parley | Explore Primeblue products: adidas.com/primeblue

XjOyIo4bszo.title: Ready For Change: adidas Legacy
XjOyIo4bszo.description:
​​Legacy is a program that helps us break barriers in sport and education in underrepresented communities. There are 27 schools already in the program, but @adidasHoops is just getting started.​​

We’re committing $1M to the Legacy Fund Scholarship as part of a larger $2.5M commitment to create scholarships for Black and LatinX youth in the next four years. We will partner with the United Negro College Fund to manage scholarships through 2024.​​

To learn more about the Legacy program, head to adidas.com/Legacy

Kx2kFhjAAC0.title: adidas | Sport Meets Silicon Valley: Philip DeSimone
Kx2kFhjAAC0.description:
As part of the Innovate stage of Creators Club Week, Carbon co-founder Philip DeSimone tells us about the potential of cutting edge adidas4D technology in the near future.
 
Creators Club Week is our first-ever digital festival that celebrates the best of adidas and brings creators from all over the world together with the best athletes, artists and designers – to learn, create and sweat. 

For one week, starting October 14, 2020, you will see the power of connections on three unique stages: Create, Innovate and Change.

Explore the 2020 festival lineup: https://www.adidas.com/creatorsclub
Join the Creators Club membership program to unlock exclusive rewards and experience the best of adidas: https://www.adidas.com/us/account-register
Feel the future with adidas: https://www.adidas.com/creatorsclubweek_innovate
